    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1242"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1242">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_PW1"
                    >PW</gloss>/7–2145: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1242<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-21">July 21,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss>–188. Top secret to Acting Secretary of State from the Secretary of
                    State.</p>
                <p>Referring to your No. 69 of July 19, 1945<note n="1" xml:id="d1242fn1">
                        <ref target="#d1240">Document No. 1240</ref>.</note> on the subject of
                    questions asked by the press in connection with unconditional surrender for
                    Japan:</p>
                <p>I would approve of your making reply to the questions you mention in the
                    following terms: “The policy of this Government on unconditional surrender by
                    Japan has been repeatedly stated. Elucidations of this policy were issued by the
                    President on May 8 and on June 1.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
